HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 286
BY REPRESENTATIVE OWEN
RURAL/DEVELOPMENT: Urges and requests Louisiana Economic Development to study
the feasibility of a Louisiana Rural Community Energy and Education Investment
Program
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request Louisiana Economic Development to conduct a comprehensive study
3 on the feasibility of establishing a Louisiana Rural Community Energy and
4 Education Investment Program.
5 WHEREAS, rural communities and public institutions in this state face rising energy
6 and operational costs that consume budgets already stretched thin, drawing dollars away
7 from classrooms, teachers, and the basic infrastructure on which rural life depends, with
8 federal Energy Information Administration data showing that the average retail residential
9 electricity price in this state rose over fourteen percent from 2024 to 2025, more than double
10 the national average over the same period; and
11 WHEREAS, the United States Department of Energy reports that K-12 school
12 districts nationally spend approximately eight billion dollars annually on energy, an expense
13 second only to paying the teachers themselves, and this burden falls hardest on rural school
14 systems, community and technical colleges, and local governmental entities operating on the
15 thinnest of margins; and
16 WHEREAS, between 2010 and 2020, only nineteen of this state's sixty-four parishes
17 grew in population, and the twenty-nine parishes in the northern half of the state collectively
18 lost almost thirty-seven thousand residents, and rural areas continue to experience population
19 decline, workforce shortages, and limited access to modern educational technology and
20 skilled-trades training programs; and
